cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the use of convolutional neural networks for remote sensing data analysis, which is a common application of computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of unsupervised learning and sparse representations, which are topics commonly studied in machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The paper also deals with image classification, which is a common application of information retrieval, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of deep architectures, which is a topic commonly studied in neural networks and computational neuroscience, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible category as well.
